              What are the smallest batches someone can brew before things get twitchy/unreliable? <br />I'm thinking of trying to do a lot of different gluten free beers in 2 liter bottles.<br />Even better is I found a force carbonator in my basement so this stuff could get bulk tested as soon as fermentation is done, by celiacs afflicted friend. <br /><br />My theory is that the FAIL that has been most gluten free beer, is that they are trying to imitate rice beer. If I make a smokey cherry porter the lack of barley will be less noticeable.

              

              
              
            </div>
