          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              Yup. I remember one barleywine ale batch I made a few years back, the bill was about $140 for a 5-gallon batch.<br /><br />I'm still not sure how we did it, but we managed to use 55lbs of grains to make that brew, PLUS 10 lbs of DME. and had 4oz of hops, and had 2 different yeast strains (champagne yeast for a 2nd pitching to get it to higher AC).<br /><br />We ended up at about 14%ABV, and even then it took 6 months of just sitting in the bottle to really smooth it out.

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
